      "content": "Even in small amounts, mixing alcohol with benzodiazepines like diazepam significantly increases the risk of adverse effects. The combination can amplify sedation, which may lead to increased daytime drowsiness or respiratory depression. Because of these serious risks, it is safest to avoid alcohol entirely while taking diazepam. Please check with your healthcare provider for safe suggestions for winding down.",
